**Test Structure - Auth & Protected Routes:**

| Test Group | Test Cases | What's Tested |
|---|---|---|
| Auth - Registration | 3 tests | New user registration; duplicate username rejection; missing fields validation |
| Auth - Login | 3 tests | Valid login token return; invalid password rejection; non-existent user rejection |
| Auth - Protected Routes | 6 tests | POST /posts auth requirement; token-based post creation; public GET endpoints; PUT/DELETE auth requirement |
| Auth - Ownership | 4 tests | Owner can update/delete own post; non-owner gets 403; resource ownership validation |
| Auth - Comment Protection | 4 tests | Comment creation auth requirement; public comment reading; comment ownership validation; owner deletion |

---

### 3. HTTP Request Method Pattern

All tests use **Supertest** with this pattern:

```typescript
request(app)
  .METHOD(path)
  .set("Authorization", `Bearer ${token}`)  // For authenticated requests
  .send({ ...payload })                      // For POST/PUT bodies
  .expect(statusCode)                        // Optional chaining
```

**Methods used:**
- GET: `/posts`, `/posts/:id`, `/posts/:postId/comments`, `/comments/:id`, `/health`
- POST: `/auth/register`, `/auth/login`, `/posts`, `/posts/:postId/comments`
- PUT: `/posts/:id`
- DELETE: `/posts/:id`, `/comments/:id`

---

### 4. Complete Assertion Summary

**Status Code Assertions:**
- 200 (OK): GET requests, successful POST/PUT/DELETE
- 201 (Created): POST `/auth/register`, POST `/posts`, POST comments
- 400 (Bad Request): Missing required fields in registration
- 401 (Unauthorized): Missing/invalid auth token, invalid credentials
- 403 (Forbidden): Non-owner attempting to modify/delete resources
- 404 (Not Found): Non-existent post or comment

**Data Validation Assertions:**
- Type checks: `toBe()` (string, number, boolean)
- Property existence: `toHaveProperty()`
- Array checks: `Array.isArray()`, length validation
- JWT validation: `token.split(".").length === 3`
- Exact value matching: `toBe()`
- Negation: `not.toHaveProperty()`

**Posts Endpoint Assertions:**
- GET /posts: returns 200, array with ≥4 items, each has id/title/content/userId/createdAt
- GET /posts/:id: returns 200 with specific content, returns 404 with "Post not found" error
- POST /posts (protected): returns 201, userId extracted from token
- PUT /posts/:id (protected): 200 on success, 401 without token, 403 for non-owner
- DELETE /posts/:id (protected): 200 on success, 401 without token, 403 for non-owner

**Comments Endpoint Assertions:**
- GET /posts/:postId/comments: returns 200, array with 2 items, correct shape (id/postId/userId/body/createdAt)
- GET /comments/:id: returns 200 with specific content and values, 404 for non-existent
- POST /posts/:postId/comments (protected): returns 401 without token, userId from token
- DELETE /comments/:id (protected): 200 on success, 403 for non-owner

---

### 5. Test Lifecycle & Patterns

**Setup Pattern:**
- Uses `beforeAll()` to register users and create test data
- Tokens stored in local variables
- Resources created within tests are referenced in subsequent tests

**No Cleanup:** Tests don't appear to have `afterAll()` or explicit cleanup; data persists across test runs.

**File Locations:**
- Test files: `/tests/*.test.ts`
- Source app: `../src/app.js` (imported as ES module)

This is a comprehensive test suite focused on API validation with strong emphasis on authentication, authorization, and resource ownership enforcement.

